Sweden's Linn Grant lines up a putt shot during the Scandinavian Mixed annual golf tournament on the European Tour at Halmstad Golf Club, Sweden. AFP/Pontus Lundahl/ TT News Agency HALMSTAD - Linn Grant of Sweden has made history in golf. She's the first woman to win a European Tour event. The 22-year-old Swede claimed victory in style at the Scandinavian Mixed at the Halmstad Golf Club. Grant won by nine strokes after an 8-under 64 in the final round. The flawless final round included eight birdies to finish at 24-under overall in front of a roaring home crowd. She finished 14 strokes clear of the next best woman, Gabriella Cowley, who tied for 15th place. Meanwhile, Scotland's Marc Warren and Sweden's Henrik Stenson finished tied for second. Grant says she hopes her victory gives a needed boost to womenâ€™s golf.